1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,295
[OLSEN]<i> Bro,</i>
<i>why was Papa's urn filled with sand?</i>

2
00:00:04,379 --> 00:00:06,214
<i>Let's think about that later.</i>

3
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:07,799
<i>It'll be far worse</i>

4
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:11,970
<i>if we, our families, and the hostages</i>
<i>are the ones turning into ashes</i>

5
00:00:12,053 --> 00:00:14,764
<i>because we're not back by twelve</i>
<i>with their money.</i>

6
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:15,765
<i>Son?</i>

7
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:17,392
<i>You know where the money is?</i>

8
00:00:17,475 --> 00:00:20,353
<i>Go to the cottage by the old docks.</i>

9
00:00:20,437 --> 00:00:21,563
<i>There's a loft there.</i>

10
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,403
<i>They've found our millions.</i>

11
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:30,780
<i>But don't celebrate yet.</i>

12
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:32,741
<i>Your mission's not over.</i>

13
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:36,036
<i>If you miss the deadline,</i>

14
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:37,495
<i>you know what will happen.</i>

15
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:39,122
<i>Bro.</i>

16
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:44,586
<i>Those guns in the gun vault</i>
<i>in the security office…</i>

17
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:46,254
<i>Think they're still there?</i>

18
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:54,637
[EMIL] <i>How's the tunnel, Engineer?</i>

19
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:57,932
[MIKE] <i>The surface is muddy,</i>
<i>but the bottom is solid.</i>

20
00:00:58,558 --> 00:01:01,186
<i>If the ground is hard, then blow it up.</i>

21
00:01:02,228 --> 00:01:03,813
[EXPLOSION]

22
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:10,945
<i>In no time, our millions</i>
<i>will be in our hands.</i>

23
00:01:11,029 --> 00:01:13,114
<i>The delivery boys are on their way back.</i>

24
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:16,951
<i>Do you know Homer personally?</i>

25
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:18,536
<i>I know his boss.</i>

26
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:21,289
<i>He was a regular VIP at La Playa Roja.</i>

27
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:24,083
<i>His bodyguard, it turns out,</i>
<i>was Lucas' brother.</i>

28
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:32,300
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

29
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:34,052
Mr. Senator.

30
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:37,347
Long time no see.

31
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:42,560
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,771
We'll have a talk later.

33
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,072
Surprised, Mr. Roja?

34
00:01:55,865 --> 00:01:58,535
You thought I'd rot in jail.

35
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:00,537
Huh?

36
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:05,250
I've waited a long time
for this day, you bastard!

37
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,293
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [LUCAS] Get him, Homer!

38
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:09,254
[GRETA] Stop it!

39
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:11,631
Have mercy!

40
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:14,509
[MAGNUS COUGHING]

41
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:16,261
Please, have mercy.

42
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:21,558
- [MAGNUS GROANING]
- Wendy?

43
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:29,816
<i>What really happened?</i>
<i>Why did you leave the resort?</i>

44
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:32,777
<i>Homer, I don't want to talk about it.</i>

45
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:35,071
<i>I will take care of you.</i>

46
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,368
[MAGNUS GRUNTS]

47
00:02:44,247 --> 00:02:45,248
You know her?

48
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:51,588
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

49
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:16,654
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:51,397
[LABORED BREATHING]

51
00:03:58,738 --> 00:03:59,948
[GROANS SOFTLY]

52
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:05,536
[GROANS AGAIN]

53
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:11,084
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:04:27,558 --> 00:04:30,561
[GROANING]

55
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:50,873
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

56
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:58,214
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:20,778
[PANTING, GROANING SOFTLY]

58
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:29,787
- [MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL]
- [SOFT BANGING]

59
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:46,137
[OBJECTS THUDDING]

60
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:56,147
Hey! No! Don't!

61
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,607
Fin!

62
00:05:57,690 --> 00:06:01,027
- Are you okay? What happened to you?
- Chef Luna.

63
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:03,196
Why are you still here?

64
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:05,406
We got stuck.

65
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,492
Now we can't get out.

66
00:06:07,575 --> 00:06:09,452
There's nothing we can do.

67
00:06:09,535 --> 00:06:10,578
We're trapped.

68
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:12,622
All the entrances and exits have bombs.

69
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:17,335
So we're looking for a way
to save Liam and Olsen.

70
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:19,670
They're hostages again, Luna.

71
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:21,964
Even the senator and his son are.

72
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:23,508
They even got Rita.

73
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,968
They're on the fourth floor.

74
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,762
There may still be hostages there.

75
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:30,264
They need our help, Luna.

76
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:33,976
[JOY] We just didn't know what to do.

77
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,687
How are we going to fight
against their guns

78
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:38,397
and all those bombs?

79
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:41,400
We need weapons.

80
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:47,615
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

81
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:50,326
Men, listen up.

82
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:52,995
Escort them back straight and clean.

83
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,455
Don't make a fuss.

84
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:57,542
We can't afford to risk any harm
to the hostages, okay?

85
00:07:02,922 --> 00:07:04,006
Sir.

86
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,341
Lieutenant Areza.

87
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:08,594
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,555
[CABRAL] What are you doing here?

89
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:12,473
I know I can help you, sir.

90
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:15,768
Areza,

91
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,895
you'll have a hard time
in your current state.

92
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:19,647
I can do it, sir.

93
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:22,233
I'm trained for bomb disposal.

94
00:07:22,817 --> 00:07:24,485
I know I can be of use.

95
00:07:25,736 --> 00:07:27,822
I've talked to the bomb squad.

96
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:30,616
There are booby traps at the entrances
and exits of the building.

97
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,493
There's an IED at the door.

98
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:33,619
Once it is opened,

99
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:37,248
the trigger hits the firing mechanism,
and it blows up.

100
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:39,625
We also saw a connection on the inside.

101
00:07:40,376 --> 00:07:42,795
We can't possibly move it
even an inch, sir.

102
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:47,550
We'll think of a way to get inside
and defuse the bombs.

103
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:53,306
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:07:59,395 --> 00:08:00,980
- Wendy…
- [WENDY BREATHES HEAVILY]

105
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:03,649
[GROANS SOFTLY]

106
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:07,236
He's the bodyguard
Wendy was telling me about.

107
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:10,364
Bodyguard of a VIP at the resort.

108
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:13,159
- [SHARP EXHALE]
- [GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:15,912
Turns out Wendy keeps a lot of secrets.

110
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:19,081
You two, move over there.

111
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:20,791
I need to watch you closely.

112
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,043
[MAN] Move!

113
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:23,127
[GRUNTS]

114
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:28,674
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

115
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:42,813
[AMBULANCE SIREN BLARING]

116
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:44,273
[LIAM EXHALES]

117
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:50,488
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:08:57,870 --> 00:09:00,122
Are you still thinking about
your father's ashes?

119
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:04,126
[SIGHS DEEPLY] What do you think, bro?

120
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:08,089
Do you think my mother knows
it only contains sand?

121
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,424
She probably does, right?

122
00:09:11,425 --> 00:09:14,345
Where could…

123
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:17,807
Where could his real ashes be?

124
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:20,393
We don't know the answer to that yet.

125
00:09:22,311 --> 00:09:24,438
That's why we need to focus first.

126
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:28,859
Let's think of how we'll get this through.

127
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:35,783
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:43,749
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

129
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,001
[WENDY] Let go of me!

130
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:47,753
Why are you also here?

131
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:52,216
I was at La Playa Roja
when the hostage taking happened.

132
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,635
You told me you wouldn't go back there.

133
00:09:55,219 --> 00:09:56,262
Brother?

134
00:09:57,346 --> 00:10:00,850
Is she the woman you said
you used to live with?

135
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:05,187
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

136
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:11,110
- [MUSIC TURNS TENSE]
- [GRUNTING, GROANING]

137
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:16,574
<i>What's going on?!</i>

138
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:18,618
<i>Damn you!</i> [GROANS]

139
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:24,081
<i>Homer, that's enough!</i>

140
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,168
- [GUN COCKS]
<i>- Go on!</i>

141
00:10:29,253 --> 00:10:31,922
<i>- Please don't.</i>
<i>- Leave! Go away!</i>

142
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,050
[POLICE CAR HONKS]

143
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,343
<i>What's happening, Homer?</i>

144
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:36,636
<i>Get the keys.</i>

145
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:43,851
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

146
00:10:43,934 --> 00:10:46,354
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

147
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,938
[HOMER] <i>Give me that.</i>

148
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:56,947
[CAR ENGINE REVS]

149
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:02,244
<i>Why are you avoiding the police?</i>

150
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:05,247
<i>Homer.</i>

151
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:08,793
<i>Speak up. What's the problem?</i>

152
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:13,589
<i>My brother and I have a business.</i>

153
00:11:13,672 --> 00:11:15,549
<i>Brother?</i>

154
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,884
<i>Who is he?</i>

155
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:18,761
<i>You'll find out soon.</i>

156
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:21,847
<i>But, for now, we need</i>
<i>to find a place to hide.</i>

157
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:23,474
<i>We need to lie low.</i>

158
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,768
<i>What did you get into?</i>

159
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:28,687
<i>Wendy, this is also for us.</i>

160
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:32,233
<i>When I finally save up enough,</i>
<i>we're going to get married.</i>

161
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:38,864
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:40,866
[RETCHES]

163
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,368
<i>Stop right here.</i>

164
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,919
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

165
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:55,756
[VOMITS]

166
00:11:56,924 --> 00:11:58,342
<i>Are you okay?</i>

167
00:11:58,426 --> 00:11:59,844
<i>Huh?</i>

168
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:05,224
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:12:05,307 --> 00:12:06,934
[HOMER] <i>Are you all right?</i>

170
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:11,230
<i>Let's get going then.</i>

171
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:17,945
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYS]

172
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,168
[DOOR OPENS]

173
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:34,837
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:37,715
<i>- Are you done?</i>
<i>- I am.</i>

175
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:38,924
[INHALES SHARPLY]

176
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,767
<i>Are you pregnant, Wendy?</i>

177
00:12:49,351 --> 00:12:51,437
<i>Oh, I'm not.</i>

178
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:53,898
<i>False alarm.</i>

179
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:59,153
[HOMER SIGHS DEEPLY]

180
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:01,655
<i>Are you sure?</i>

181
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:04,658
<i>You've been feeling nauseous for days.</i>

182
00:13:04,742 --> 00:13:08,662
<i>The doctor said</i>
<i>it's because of hyperacidity.</i>

183
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:14,919
<i>I'm leaving for La Playa Roja</i>
<i>to accompany my boss.</i>

184
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:17,421
<i>I'll be away for about three days.</i>
<i>Then I'll come home.</i>

185
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:19,840
<i>Take care.</i>

186
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:22,134
<i>Take care of yourself too.</i>

187
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:27,389
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:29,350
<i>I'll get going then.</i>

189
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:32,436
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

190
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:49,912
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:59,672
[SIRENS BLASTING IN DISTANCE]

192
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:02,550
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

193
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:06,512
Men, let them through!

194
00:14:06,595 --> 00:14:12,268
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:17,022
[SIRENS BLARING]

196
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:39,295
[DADO] Oh, kids. Welcome home!

197
00:14:39,795 --> 00:14:41,547
Hurry up.

198
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:46,927
That's a lot!

199
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:50,681
[FAINT OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

200
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:52,600
Want to help us carry all this?

201
00:14:52,683 --> 00:14:53,559
[PANICKED CRIES]

202
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:55,603
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

203
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:57,730
Get down!

204
00:14:57,813 --> 00:14:59,565
[CHUCKLES]

205
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:06,655
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

206
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:10,701
Liam. The phone.

207
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:11,994
[LUGGAGE SLIDES]

208
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,292
[DADO] Good job.

209
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:21,879
[SNIFFS, SIGHS HAPPILY]

210
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:24,506
You want some?

211
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:26,800
[DADO] It's hot, right?
This can be your fan.

212
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:27,927
Get that inside.

213
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:33,515
Help us carry this.

214
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:39,188
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,397
Let's go.

216
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:46,362
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

217
00:15:50,824 --> 00:15:53,661
It's not just money
you'll get here, Homer.

218
00:15:55,245 --> 00:15:57,998
You'll also get back the woman you let go.

219
00:15:58,582 --> 00:15:59,792
[HOMER] Boss.

220
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,127
I didn't let go of her.

221
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:05,130
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,092
- She ran away from me.
- Let go of me!

223
00:16:08,175 --> 00:16:10,552
Why are you so disgusted?

224
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:13,555
Back then, I was quick
to convince you to join me.

225
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,933
Because I thought you were a good person.

226
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:18,060
Ah.

227
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,938
The woman with no dirt has spoken.

228
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:24,566
You're a criminal too, aren't you?

229
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:29,863
You were imprisoned for ten years
because of fraud.

230
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:32,783
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

231
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:36,328
Boss, looks like you know
a lot about Wendy.

232
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:42,042
When Jacinto and I were planning this,

233
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:47,423
we agreed to just scare the hostages.

234
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:50,050
He said we shouldn't hurt anybody.

235
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:52,428
Except for one person.

236
00:16:52,511 --> 00:16:55,139
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:58,017
And then he showed me your picture.

238
00:17:00,602 --> 00:17:03,355
That's when I learned of your background.

239
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:08,485
That you raised your child alone.

240
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:13,323
No one should get hurt aside from me?

241
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,200
[SHORT LAUGH]

242
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:19,121
You were even a special mention.

243
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:22,666
Sounds like Jacinto's very mad at you.

244
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,251
I don't know him!

245
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:28,255
So why is he targeting you?

246
00:17:28,338 --> 00:17:31,842
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

247
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:33,177
Homer.

248
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:39,183
Looks like someone has
a lot of anger toward your ex.

249
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:41,727
Someone connected to Jacinto.

250
00:17:42,686 --> 00:17:45,189
[EMIL] Whoever that is

251
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:50,611
was also part of orchestrating

252
00:17:51,487 --> 00:17:53,113
this mess.

253
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:59,870
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

254
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:24,436
[OLSEN PANTS]

255
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:28,774
[GRUNTS]

256
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:36,365
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:40,285
[OLSEN] Why don't you help me?

258
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,831
- [DADO] Hurry up.
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

259
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:47,209
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

260
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:52,589
[SOFT GROAN]

261
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:58,637
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

262
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,859
<i>Don't think for a second</i>

263
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:14,027
<i>that I've forgotten about</i>
<i>what you did to my brother.</i>

264
00:19:14,111 --> 00:19:16,321
<i>Your brother died because of you.</i>

265
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:18,782
- [LIAM GROANS]
<i>- No!</i>

266
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:23,912
[OVERLAPPING SHOUTING,
SCREAMING]

267
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:28,250
[OVERLAPPING SHOUTING,
SCREAMING]

268
00:19:32,796 --> 00:19:35,174
<i>What's happening? Doc!</i>

269
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:37,634
<i>- It's like she can't breathe!</i>
<i>- I need to get a nebulizer.</i>

270
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:42,806
<i>So you're still alive.</i>

271
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:44,474
<i>You're dead.</i>

272
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:47,477
[BOTH GRUNTING]

273
00:19:57,613 --> 00:20:00,866
<i>I didn't want to have any connection</i>
<i>with you anymore.</i>

274
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:03,869
<i>I got into that trade</i>
<i>because I wanted to save</i>

275
00:20:03,952 --> 00:20:06,413
<i>a huge amount of money</i>
<i>for our future family.</i>

276
00:20:06,496 --> 00:20:07,623
<i>- Wendy--</i>
<i>- You bastard!</i>

277
00:20:08,498 --> 00:20:10,167
<i>- Come on!</i>
<i>- That's enough!</i>

278
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:12,586
[HOMER] <i>Well?!</i>

279
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:13,879
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

280
00:20:14,504 --> 00:20:16,006
- [MINNIE COUGHING, GROANING]
<i>- Hon.</i>

281
00:20:16,089 --> 00:20:20,552
<i>Daddy, Mommy's sick again.</i>

282
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:22,763
<i>No, baby.</i>

283
00:20:23,847 --> 00:20:25,557
<i>Mommy can handle this.</i>

284
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,977
<i>Remember my promise to you?</i>

285
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:32,356
<i>- That we'll get back home?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

286
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:34,900
[MIKE] <i>Once you break through,</i>

287
00:20:34,983 --> 00:20:37,486
<i>you'll have an exit path</i>
<i>out of this hospital.</i>

288
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,654
[EMIL] <i>Liam Roja.</i>

289
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:43,575
<i>If you aren't back here in five minutes,</i>

290
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,870
<i>you know what'll happen to your mom.</i>
